**`GET /orders`** — Parse `userId` string to number (`parseInt`, guard on `isNaN`), pass `status` through as string. Call `listOrders({ userId, status })`. No error paths, but wrap for consistency. `res.json(result)`.

**`GET /orders/:id`** — Parse id. Try/catch wrapping `getOrder(id)`. On `ServiceError` respond with its `statusCode` and `message`. On success `res.json(result)`.

